President Trump congratulates Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania on the 100th anniversary of their independence. He emphasizes the United States' continued recognition of the sovereignty of the Baltic republics and discusses cooperation on trade, investment, and security initiatives. He also expresses concern about the trade deficit with China and the theft of intellectual property. In regards to immigration, President Trump mentions the caravan of people coming to the U.S. from Honduras and the need for stronger immigration laws and border security. He also addresses the issue of NATO spending and his desire to have a good relationship with Russia. President Trump criticizes the postal subsidies received by Amazon and talks about the impact of online retail on brick-and-mortar stores. The President concludes by mentioning his hope that Scott Pruitt, the head of the Environmental Protection Agency, will do a great job.